### StatefulWidget

A `StatefulWidget` creates a `State` object that holds mutable state. The widget can rebuild when state changes.

```dart
class CounterWidget extends StatefulWidget {
  const CounterWidget({super.key});

  @override
  State<CounterWidget> createState() => _CounterWidgetState();
}

class _CounterWidgetState extends State<CounterWidget> {
  int _count = 0; // Mutable state

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Column(
      children: [
        Text('Count: $_count'),
        ElevatedButton(
          onPressed: () {
            setState(() {
              _count++;
            });
          },
          child: const Text('Increment'),
        ),
      ],
    );
  }
}
```

### State Lifecycle

| Method | Called |
|--------|--------|
| `initState()` | First time widget is inserted |
| `didChangeDependencies()` | Dependencies change |
| `didUpdateWidget()` | Parent rebuilds with new config |
| `build()` | When state or config changes |
| `setState()` | Trigger rebuild |
| `dispose()` | Widget is removed permanently |

```dart
class _MyState extends State<MyWidget> {
  @override
  void initState() {
    super.initState();
    // Initialize controllers, listeners, etc.
  }

  @override
  void dispose() {
    // Clean up controllers
    super.dispose();
  }

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return const Placeholder();
  }
}
```

### setState()

`setState()` marks the widget as dirty and schedules a rebuild.

```dart
void _updateName(String newName) {
  setState(() {
    _name = newName;
  });
}
```

### StatefulWidget vs StatelessWidget

| Aspect | StatelessWidget | StatefulWidget |
|--------|----------------|----------------|
| Mutable state | No | Yes |
| Rebuild trigger | Parent rebuild | `setState()` |
| Performance | More efficient | Can be less efficient |
| Use case | Static content | Dynamic content |

> **Key Point:** Minimize StatefulWidgets. Extract parts that don't need state into StatelessWidgets. Call `setState()` only when needed to avoid unnecessary rebuilds.

